caption: Was never a fan of empanadas, however, a friend of mine swore she could change my mind. This was my last and final try on them and now I’m obsessed! The best empanadas come from this truck right here! I’ve tried most of the empanadas, but my favourite hands down has got to be the chicken and cheese! I swear by these and ask her to bring me home a couple at least once a week since she works right by the truck! God bless her and Cesar for these amazing empanadas. I understand why there is usually a long line up for them.
By far the best empanadas in NYC. Whenever I am in the area I stop by and order 3 beef with cheese and an extra 3 to take home along with a banana and Nutella desert empanada

Cesar makes incredible fried empandas for about $3 each. They are crunchy and warm and filled with goodness. I love the beef and cheese, the spinach, the chicken with veggies, the guava. They also do burritos and plates and tacos, but when I see the truck all I crave are the empanadas. Note that Cesar has three vehicles and you may see any or all of them: a big white truck with two windows that does tacos and plates, a bright blue truck for Cesar's cafe that carries everything, and a small coffee kiosk style cart that only carries empanadas. Cash is preferred, and you MUST get the green salsa.

1st there was not enough meat in the empanadas and 2nd the drippings from the empanadas fell onto my coat (my fault), but the smell of the drippings left a terribly foul odor (from the onion). 3rd the empanadas are over priced. I know some Spanish restaurants that charge far less for better quality of empanadas with MEAT.

I was filling up the tank tonight on Flushing Are. And hungry as hell. Cesar's Empanadas truck pulled in to fill up. As he passed me to pay inside I said "Got any left?" He waved me off. No, no... He waved me off again as he came out. Poor guy, I thought -people probably stop him at every corner. As I went round to get back in my car, he opened the order window and waved me over. He handed me a bag with 4 hot beef empanadas in it. Yikes!! The absolute best! Hands down. Bless up that man!

I ordered two, or should I say my boyfriend ordered me two ( can you say cha-ching? $$$) Well anyway, the ones I got were chicken and cheese, one of each. They were flaky, moist, and de-lic-ious. I enjoyed them on the LIRR as the lady sitting across fro me jealously stared. Go get your own!!!!!! I washed it all down with a signature Cesar's Cafe cup o' Joe. the empanadas are outdone by nothing lest it be their coffee. This coffee was the best coffee I've ever had. ever. had. It was robust but also light but also smooth as a babies bottom. 5 stars to this food truck, RUN , don't walk to Cesar's

Empanadas and quesadillas served curbside at the LIRR entrance to Atlantic Terminal. Great veggie street-food options. My favorites are the spinach & cheese and guava & cheese. There's almost always a line, but it moves quickly. Service is fast and friendly.  EDIT - the empanadas are best earlier in the day. I've had a couple of dried-out misses in the early evening.
